title: Trump’s ‘white genocide’ claims ignore the reality of life and crime in South Africa
description: US president intoned ‘death, death, death’ as he waved articles purporting to show violence against white minority It was an ambush crafted straight from a reality-TV playbook. The Oval Office meeting with South Africa’s president, Cyril Ramaphosa, started with exchanges of pleasantries, before Donald Trump said “turn the lights down” and a video was played to support his false claims that white South African farmers are being murdered for their race.Ramaphosa came prepared with champion white South African golfers Ernie Els and Retief Goosen, whom the golf-mad Trump referred to as “friends”, as well as South Africa’s richest person, Johann Rupert. title: Donald Trump signs executive orders to accelerate US nuclear development
description: Donald Trump has signed orders to boost nuclear power. The aim is to quadruple production in 25 years. This involves easing regulations and speeding up reactor approvals. The move addresses rising electricity demand from data centres and AI. The US seeks to win the AI race with China.

title: No runway lights, weather system wasn't working: What we know so far about San Diego plane crash
description: A Cessna 550 Citation crashed near San Diego's Montgomery-Gibbs Executive Airport, likely killing six, including music executive Dave Shapiro. The crash occurred in heavy fog with runway lights out and a disabled weather alert system. The pilot, aware of the conditions, attempted the landing after a flight from New Jersey, refueling in Kansas.
author: TOI World Desk
